    "narrative": "The Austin Waves are staring down a slate defined by aggressive matchup exploitation, with **Jackson Merrill** headlining the roster at a dominant 75.10 efficiency score. His favorable encounter against Feltner provides the day\u2019s highest ceiling, bolstered significantly by a 14% park factor boost and a 15% SP skill advantage that makes him an elite start. Conversely, the top of the order remains a point of emphasis for offensive volume; **Drake Baldwin** (61.45) and **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (57.07) are prioritized for their #2 spots in the lineup, with **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** specifically benefiting from a +14% boost via his dynamic platoon advantage against Ritchie. \n\nWe are exercising caution with several high-profile bats facing stiff resistance today. While **Kyle Tucker** (51.92) and **Heliot Ramos** (50.47) provide respectable utility, they are suppressed by low SP skill scores against Logan Webb and Glasnow, respectively. **Marcell Ozuna** (44.24) remains a volatile play; his projection is currently hindered by a pending lineup status and a history of struggle against deGrom (BvP -3%). **Josh Jung** (41.26) was the most difficult exclusion from the starting nine, ultimately losing his spot because the baseline efficiency of our active infield depth against arguably softer competition provides a higher floor for Roto categories. We are continuing to monitor **Jordan Westburg** on the IL and navigating the absence of **Gunnar Henderson** and **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** due to today\u2019s schedule, forcing us to lean heavily on the remaining active core to chase stolen base opportunities where speed factors\u2014specifically the slow delivery of opposing pitchers\u2014remain our primary leverage point for **Luis Robert Jr.** and **Andy Pages**.",
